{"title_page": "Lakeridge High School", "text_new": "{{Infobox school\n| name              = Lakeridge High School\n| image             = Lakeridge High School.jpg\n| image_size        = 250px\n| streetaddress     = 1235 Overlook Drive\n| city              = [[Lake Oswego, Oregon|Lake Oswego]]\n| county            = <!--[[Clackamas County, Oregon|Clackamas]]-->\n| state             = [[Oregon]]\n| zipcode           = 97034\n| country           = [[United States]]\n| coordinates       = {{Coord|45.397|-122.694|type:edu_source:googlemaps_region:US-OR|display=inline,title}} <!-- geocoded street address and centered on entrance -->\n| type              = [[Public school (government funded)|Public]]\n| district          = [[Lake Oswego School District|Lake Oswego S.D.]]\n| principal         = Desiree Fisher\n| grades            = 9\u201312\n| students          = 1,111 (2017\u201318)<ref name=NCES>{{cite web|url=https://nces.ed.gov/ccd/schoolsearch/school_detail.asp?Search=1&DistrictID=4107230&ID=410723000069|title=Lakeridge High School|publisher=National Center for Education Statistics|accessdate=December 15, 2019}}</ref>\n| ratio             = 19.81<ref name=NCES/>\n| teaching_staff    = 56.08 (FTE)<ref name=NCES/>\n| rival             = [[Lake Oswego High School|Lake Oswego Lakers]]\n| mascot            =\n| mascot image      =\n| team_name         = Pacers <ref name=\"OSAA\">{{cite web |title=Lakeridge High School |url=http://www.osaa.org/schools/38 |website=Full Member Schools |publisher=Oregon School Athletics Association |accessdate=8 April 2019}}</ref>\n| colors            = Columbia blue, Vegas gold\n{{Color box|#75B2DD|border=darkgray}} {{Color box|#C5B358|border=darkgray}} <ref name=\"OSAA\" />\n| conference        = Three Rivers 6A-5<br>([[Oregon School Activities Association|OSAA]]) <ref name=\"OSAA\" />\n| newspaper         = ''[http://lakeridgenewspacer.com/ The Newspacer]''\n| yearbook          = ''Symposium''\n| established       = 1971\n| homepage          = [http://lhs.loswego.k12.or.us lhs.loswego.k12.or.us]\n}}\n'''Lakeridge High School''' is a four-year [[State school|public]] [[secondary school]] in [[Lake Oswego, Oregon]], a suburb south of [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]]. The second high school in the [[Lake Oswego School District]], it first opened in 1971.\n\n==Academics==\nIn 1987, Lakeridge High School was honored in the [[Blue Ribbon Schools Program]], the highest honor a school can receive in the United States.<ref name=\"blueribbon\">[http://www.ed.gov/programs/nclbbrs/list-1982.pdf Archived: Blue Ribbon Schools Program, Schools Recognized 1982-1983 Through 1999-2002 (PDF)<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090326055622/http://www.ed.gov/programs/nclbbrs/list-1982.pdf |date=2009-03-26 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, 90% of the school's seniors received a [[high school diploma]]. Of 261 students, 234 graduated, 15 dropped out, nine received a [[Oregon modified high school diploma|modified diploma]], and three were still in high school in 2009.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/education/index.ssf/2009/06/high_school_dropout_rates.html|title=State releases high school graduation rates|date=2009-06-30|work=[[The Oregonian]]|accessdate=2009-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.oregonlive.com/education_impact/2009/06/Dropout-Rates.xls|title=Oregon dropout rates for 2008|date=2009-06-30|work=[[The Oregonian]]|accessdate=2009-07-01}}</ref>\n\nThe school received a silver ranking in ''[[U.S. News & World Report]]''{{'}}s 2010 \"America's Best High Schools\" survey.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/listings/high-schools/oregon/lakeridge_high_school|title=Best High Schools 2010|date=2009-12-09|work=[[U.S. News & World Report]]|accessdate=2010-01-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/education/index.ssf/2010/01/nine_oregon_high_schools_ranke.html|title= Nine Oregon high schools ranked among best in nation |last=Graves|first=Bill|date=2010-01-15|work=[[The Oregonian]]|accessdate=2010-01-16}}</ref>\n\n== Notable alumni ==\n* [[Marisa Abegg]], professional soccer player\n* [[J. J. Birden]] - former NFL wide receiver<ref name=\"OregonLive\">{{cite web|title=J.J. Birden |publisher=[[OregonLive]]|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/collegefootball/index.ssf/2015/08/sunday_morning_news_notes_link_17.html | accessdate=October 11, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Erin Chambers]] - actress, played Siobhan on ''General Hospital''\n* [[Travis Cole]] - former NFL and Arena Football League player, and ironically not very good at football\n* [[Jillian Harmon]] - collegiate and Olympic basketball player<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gostanford.com/sports/w-baskbl/mtt/harmon_jillian00.html |title=Jillian Harmon |publisher=GoStanford.com |accessdate=May 11, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403191534/http://www.gostanford.com/sports/w-baskbl/mtt/harmon_jillian00.html |archivedate=April  3, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wnba.com/draft2009/profiles/prospect_harmon_jillian.html |title=Jillian Harmon |publisher=WBNA.com |accessdate=May 11, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090408074950/http://www.wnba.com/draft2009/profiles/prospect_harmon_jillian.html |archivedate=April  8, 2009 }}</ref>\n* [[C. W. Jensen]] - retired Portland police captain, TV personality\n* [[Kennedy (commentator)|Kennedy]] - former MTV VJ, political satirist \n* [[Cathy Marshall (news anchor)|Cathy Marshall]] - news anchor<ref name=\"kgw-bio\">{{cite web|title=Cathy Marshall <nowiki>[biography]</nowiki>|publisher=[[KGW]]|url=http://www.kgw.com/on-tv/bios/147815645.html|accessdate=May 5, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120428154246/http://www.kgw.com/on-tv/bios/147815645.html|archive-date=April 28, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Sam Martin (singer)|Sam Martin]] - professional singer, songwriter \n* [[Bart Miadich]] - [[Major League Baseball]] pitcher also appeared in Mitchell Report as steroid user. <ref>https://www.baseball-reference.com/players/m/miadiba01.shtml</ref>\n* [[Doug Nussmeier]] - [[National Football League|NFL]] quarterback, college football coach; class of 1989 <ref name=ncush>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=zudVAAAAIBAJ&sjid=seEDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6766,2747647&dq=nussmeier&hl=en |newspaper=Eugene Register-Guard |last=Kayfes |first=Dave |title=North comes up short against Lakeridge, 54-48 |date=March 11, 1989 |page=7C}}</ref><ref name=diaaid>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=cVBYAAAAIBAJ&sjid=wIYDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6388%2C2135539|newspaper=The Bulletin |location=[[Bend, Oregon|Bend, OR]] |agency=Associated Press |last=Baum |first=Bob |title=Division I-AA Idaho hopes to Vandalize the favored Ducks|date=September 14, 1990 |page=D-1 }}</ref>\n* [[Jason Palumbis]] - football player, [[Stanford Cardinal football|Stanford University]] [[quarterback]]; class of 1987 <ref name=wadaycm>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=otwzAAAAIBAJ&sjid=hOEDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6625,3527696&dq=palumbis+lakeridge&hl=en|newspaper=Eugene Register-Guard |last=Kayfes |first=Dave |title=What a difference a year can make |date=October 14, 1986|page=2D}}</ref><!--{{Citation needed|date=July 2010}}-->\n* [[Erik Wilhelm]] - NFL quarterback, [[Cincinnati Bengals]]; class of 1984 <ref name=bphop>{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=7JFTAAAAIBAJ&sjid=AIcDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6476,4884079&dq=wilhelm+lakeridge&hl=en|newspaper=The Bulletin |location=[[Bend, Oregon|Bend, OR]] |agency=UPI |title=Beavers pin hopes on pass|date=August 20, 1985 |page=D-1 }}</ref>\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==Further reading==\n\n* Kyle Swenson, [https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2017/11/03/ore-teen-was-excited-to-join-her-high-school-dance-team-then-she-learned-about-the-maple-syrup-wrestling/ \"Oregon Teen was Excited to Join her High School Dance Team. Then She Learned About the Maple Syrup Wrestling,\"] ''Washing