{"title_page": "Realty One Group", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=November 2019}}\n{{Advert|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n'''Realty ONE Group''' (stylized: Realty ONE Group) is an American real-estate brokerage with corporate offices in [[Laguna Niguel, California]].<ref name=SlindFlor>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2012-03-28/kimberly-clark-rda-micro-facebook-intellectual-property#p2 |title=Kimberly-Clark, RDA Micro, Facebook: Intellectual Property |date=March 28, 2012 |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |author=Victoria Slind-Flor |magazine=[[Businessweek]]}}</ref>{{Infobox company\n| name                = Realty ONE Group\n| logo                = realty_ONE_Group_Logo_Black_Text.png\n| type                = [[Private company|Private]]\n| traded_as           = \n| fate                = \n| predecessor         = \n| successor           = \n| foundation          = {{Start date|2005|MM|}}\n| founder             = [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuba_Jewgieniew Kuba Jewgieniew]\n| defunct             = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location            = \n| location_city       = \n| locations           = \n| area_served         = \n| key_people          = [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuba_Jewgieniew Kuba Jewgieniew], Mike Clear, Vinnie Tracey, Alexandru D. Mihai, Esq., Cory Vasquez, and Gary Fabian\n| products            = \n| services            = \n| revenue             = \n| operating_income    = \n| net_income          = \n| aum                 = <!-- Only used with financial services companies -->\n| assets              = \n| equity              = \n| owner               = \n| num_employees       = \n| parent              = \n| divisions           = \n| subsid              = \n| footnotes           = \n| location_country    = [[Laguna Niguel, California]], [[United States of America]]\n| homepage            = {{URL|https://www.realtyonegroup.com}}\n| intl                = \n}}\n\n==Company overview==\nRealty ONE Group was founded in 2005<ref name=Buchholz /> by owner and CEO [[Kuba Jewgieniew]],<ref name=rtinc /> a former stockbroker.<ref name=Wargotwo>{{cite news |url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2010/apr/16/q-kuba-jewgieniew-ceo-realty-one-group/ |title=Q&A: Kuba Jewgieniew, CEO of Realty ONE Group |author=Buck Wargo |newspaper=[[Las Vegas Sun]] |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |date=April 16, 2010}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nRealty ONE Group expanded into Arizona in 2007,<ref name=\"Buchholz\" /> and by August 2010, the company had 2,200 agents.<ref name=\"Wargotwo\" /> In August 2011 the brokerage acquired John Hall & Associates, a [[Phoenix, Arizona]]-based real estate brokerage.<ref name=\"Buchholz\">{{cite news |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/phoenix/news/2011/08/09/john-hall-associates-acquired-by.html |title=John Hall & Associates acquired by Realty One Group |date=August 9, 2011 |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |newspaper=[[Phoenix Business Journal]] |author=Jan Buchholz}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.inman.com/news/2011/08/10/realty-one-group-acquires-john-hall-associates |date=August 10, 2011 |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |publisher=Inman News |title=Realty One Group acquires John Hall & Associates}}</ref> The brokerage had also expanded into the State of California in January 2010,<ref name=\"Wargotwo\" /> and opened offices in Orange County and Riverside County by the end of 2011.<ref name=\"Wargo\">{{cite news |author=Buck Wargo |url=http://www.vegasinc.com/news/2011/sep/12/realty-one-group-out-compete-nationally/ |date=September 11, 2011 |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |newspaper=[[Las Vegas Sun]] |title=Realty One Group out to compete nationally}}</ref> In 2012 Realty ONE Group opened Realty ONE Group Affiliates, the official franchise arm of the company.<ref>{{cite article |url=http://www.inman.com/news/2012/08/15/realty-one-group-expands-franchising |author=Paul Hagey |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |date=August 15, 2012 |title=Realty One Group expands into franchising |publisher=Inman News}}</ref>\n\nRealty ONE Group opened its first international office in February 2019 in [[Leduc, Alberta]], Canada and opened its second in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada in June 2019.\n\nBecause of its swift growth in both office and agent count, Realty ONE Group was named one of the fastest growing companies in the U.S.by [[Inc. 500]] from 2009 to 2014.<ref name=\"rtinc\">{{cite web |url=http://www.realtytoday.com/articles/4058/20130402/realty-one-group-takes-7th-spot-real-trends-500-list.htm |title=Realty ONE Group Takes 7th Spot in Real Trend's 500 List |date=April 2, 2013 |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |publisher=Realty Today}}</ref>\n\n== Business Strategy ==\n[[Kuba Jewgieniew]], who has been named to Swanepoel\u2019s Top 200 Most Powerful People in Residential Real Estate a number of times,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swanepoel.com/power200/2017|title=2017 Swanepoel POWER 200|website=www.swanepoel.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-25}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/902443817 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/856432185 cite #5 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC bot/Job 18]]}}</ref> created the company to be different from traditional real estate brokerages. Realty ONE Group pays agents 100% of their commission and only charges a flat monthly fee to be part of a franchise,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2010/apr/16/q-kuba-jewgieniew-ceo-realty-one-group/ |title=Q&A: Kuba Jewgieniew, CEO of Realty ONE Group |author=Buck Wargo |newspaper=[[Las Vegas Sun]] |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |date=April 16, 2010}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/902443817 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/856432185 cite #4 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC bot/Job 18]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Buck Wargo |url=http://www.vegasinc.com/news/2011/sep/12/realty-one-group-out-compete-nationally/ |date=September 11, 2011 |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |newspaper=[[Las Vegas Sun]] |title=Realty One Group out to compete nationally}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/902443817 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/856432185 cite #7 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC bot/Job 18]]}}</ref> \u00a0offering comprehensive tools, technology, training and a unique company culture.\n\nRealty ONE Group is known for its contemporary offices with modern d\u00e9cor and its black and gold signature colors. The company also frequently markets itself as the \u201cUNBrokerage.\u201d\n\n== Leadership ==\nThe company is focused on future growth and continues to recruit an experienced executive leadership team.\n\nIn early 2017, with decades of prior experience at American Home Shield and HSA Home Warranty, Michael Clear joined Realty ONE Group as Chief Operating Officer. In September 2017, Realty ONE Group appointed Vinnie Tracey Realty ONE Group International President. Tracey is the former President of RE/MAX International and a 44-year veteran of the industry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://realtormag.realtor.org/daily-news/2017/09/15/realty-one-group-names-new-president|title=Realty ONE Group Names New President|website=Realtor Magazine|language=en|access-date=2017-10-25}} {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/902443817 by a bug in VisualEditor and later restored by a bot from the original cite located at Special:Permalink/856432185 cite #12 - verify the cite is accurate and delete this template. [[User:GreenC bot/Job 18]]}}</ref> Chief Financial Officer Gary Fabian joined Realty ONE Group\u2019s C-Suite in December 2018 with extensive experience with Bank of America/Countrywide Home Loans and Stearns Lending. In 2019, Cory Vasquez was promoted to Chief Marketing Officer having previously spent 11 years leading RE/MAX\u2019s corporate communications team.\n\n== Philanthropy ==\nRealty ONE Group established its own 501(c)3 organization, Realty ONE Group Cares, Inc., in 2014 as a way for the organization and its agents to give back to the community. And every year on its anniversary, May 1, the franchisor celebrates with a company-wide day of giving back and volunteering. The anniversary day is called ONE Day.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.realtyonegroup.com/ Realty ONE Group]\n\n[[Category:Real estate companies of the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=November 2019}}\n{{Advert|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n'''Realty ONE Group''' (stylized: Realty ONE Group) is an American real-estate brokerage with corporate offices in [[Laguna Niguel, California]].<ref name=SlindFlor>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2012-03-28/kimberly-clark-rda-micro-facebook-intellectual-property#p2 |title=Kimberly-Clark, RDA Micro, Facebook: Intellectual Property |date=March 28, 2012 |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |author=Victoria Slind-Flor |magazine=[[Businessweek]]}}</ref>{{Infobox company\n| name                = Realty ONE Group\n| logo                = realty_ONE_Group_Logo_Black_Text.png\n| type                = [[Private company|Private]]\n| traded_as           = \n| fate                = \n| predecessor         = \n| successor           = \n| foundation          = {{Start date|2005|MM|}}\n| founder             = [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuba_Jewgieniew Kuba Jewgieniew]\n| defunct             = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location            = \n| location_city       = \n| locations           = \n| area_served         = \n| key_people          = [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuba_Jewgieniew Kuba Jewgieniew], Mike Clear, Vinnie Tracey, Alexandru D. Mihai, Esq., C